<font color="#FF0000">LIGHTING AND THUNDER</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug 30 15:56:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Lightning and Thunder<br>
I rememberThe first night with guns. The first night on Hill 65, I had only been in country for about a little over a week. But now, I was assigned to a gun squad and here I believe my tour actually began.<br>
Before falling asleep, I sat on the edge of my bunk under the covered porch of gun's bunker. Keeton and John slept on the cots on top of the bunker. I had taken the middle cot on the porch. Moore slept on the cot with the air mattress on it, whom everybody called a rubber lady. Jones on the cot to my right. No one slept inside the bunker.<br>
Off in the distance, toward the Annamite mountains and the Laos/Cambodia border I could see lightning striking the ground. A short time later I heard the sound of thunder and thought it was going to rain.<br>
I looked out from under the cover and noticed that there wasn't a cloud in the sky.  <br>
It took awhile before I realized that it wasn't lightning and thunder I was seeing and hearing. <br>

